I tried the new 1-to-1 chat trying to chat with myself. The program crashes!
Windows98-like buttons appear somewhat out of place nowadays. It would not possible to make the GUI look like it is from our century?

Allow multiline messages


Enter sends the message, and even if one copies and paste text with newlines those are replaced with spaces. The current behavior is quite bad, overall when sharing pieces of code.

Allow the whole unicode


At the moment we use the UTF-16LE. Many of our customers are Mathematicians and they would like to write mathematical symbols outside the BMP. At the moment the application crashes when trying to send a non-BMP character.
